page.title: 11CHANGES
page.content: Over the last couple of years, the residents in this area have noticed a number of changes. There has been an increase in traffic, due mainly to the construction of the gas terminal, which has brought new jobs and new people to the area. The fact that people are spending more time on leisure activites, also contributes to the increase in traffic. There have been a number of houses built in the area but it is on a small scale. The sands have given growth to numerous sea plants and there is quite an expanse of green vegetation on the Rampside sands. The coastline has been reinforced by a concrete sea wall, which protects the houses and the road from flooding, in adverse weather conditions. This wall extends from Peasholmes Lane to Goudsbarrow.
